# FaceKeeper Black-Screen Fix — DO NOT REVERT

The `FaceKeeperActivity` is a transparent 1×1 activity that keeps the Jetpack XR
session host alive while Chrome runs WebXR.  If any of the safeguards below are
removed, the user sees a **black screen flash** when tapping
"Open in Chrome for WebXR (+ face)."

## Mandatory theme attributes (`Theme.FaceKeeper` in `themes.xml`)

All of these MUST remain present:

| Attribute                        | Value                       | Why                                         |
|----------------------------------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| `windowIsTranslucent`            | `true`                      | Transparent window                          |
| `windowBackground`              | `@android:color/transparent`| No opaque fill behind content               |
| `colorBackground`               | `@android:color/transparent`| Prevents system-default grey/black bg       |
| `windowNoTitle`                  | `true`                      | No title bar                                |
| `windowContentOverlay`          | `@null`                     | No content overlay shadow                   |
| `backgroundDimEnabled`          | `false`                     | No dim behind the activity                  |
| `windowDisablePreview`          | `true`                      | No "starting window" snapshot (black flash) |
| `windowAnimationStyle`          | `@null`                     | No enter/exit activity transition           |

## Mandatory code guards (`FaceKeeperActivity.kt`)

- `onCreate()` and `onResume()` MUST call `finish()` + `overridePendingTransition(0,0)`
  if `!FaceHandoffState.isChromeHandoff()`.
- `FaceKeeperActivity` MUST NEVER call `FaceHandoffState.setChromeHandoff(true)`.
  Handoff is set only from `MainActivity` / PiP / Chrome flow.

## Mandatory intent flags (`FaceKeeper.kt`)

- `acquire()` and `release()` MUST add `Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NO_ANIMATION`.
- After `startActivity()`, caller MUST call `overridePendingTransition(0, 0)`.

## Mandatory handoff logic (`FaceHandoffState.kt`, `MainActivity.kt`)

- `recordRelayPostSuccess()` is called only on successful HTTP ingest in
  `FaceHttpRelay`, never on handoff toggle.
- Cold launcher start (`ACTION_MAIN` + `CATEGORY_LAUNCHER` + no saved state)
  MUST call `clearChromeHandoff()`.
- `canRestoreHandoffSession(inPiP, pausingForChrome)` gates keeper restore —
  returns true only when handoff is active AND app is in PiP or transitioning.

## AndroidManifest.xml

`FaceKeeperActivity` MUST use `android:theme="@style/Theme.FaceKeeper"`.
